name: NestedStyleDelimiters

properties.name: SENTENCE
properties.description: Uses the first sentence or sentences in the paragraph as the nested style delimiter. The first sentence is considered all text preceding the first period, question mark, or exclamation mark in the paragraph.

properties.name: ANY_WORD
properties.description: Uses the first word or words in the paragraph as the nested style delimiter. The first word is considered all characters preceding the first space or white space character in the paragraph.

properties.name: ANY_CHARACTER
properties.description: Uses the first character or characters other than zero-width markers as the nested style delimiter. Zero-width markers include anchors, index markers, XML tags, and so on.

properties.name: LETTERS
properties.description: Uses the first alpha character or characters as the nested style delimiter. Note: To specify the number of letters, see repetition.

properties.name: DIGITS
properties.description: Uses the first numeric character or characters as the nested style delimiter. Note: To specify the number of digits, see repetition.

properties.name: TABS
properties.description: Uses the first tab character as the nested style delimiter. Note: Does not use the first tab stop. If no actual tab character has been inserted in the paragraph, the nested style is applied through the end of the paragraph.

properties.name: INLINE_GRAPHIC
properties.description: Uses the first inline graphic as the nested style delimiter.

properties.name: DROPCAP
properties.description: Uses the dropcap as the nested style delimiter.

properties.name: FORCED_LINE_BREAK
properties.description: Uses the first forced line break as the nested style delimiter.

properties.name: END_NESTED_STYLE
properties.description: Uses the inserted end nested style here character as the nested style delimiter.

properties.name: INDENT_HERE_TAB
properties.description: Uses the first indent-to-here tab character as the nested style delimiter. Note: Does not use the first indent-to-here tab stop. If no actual indent-to-here tab character has been inserted in the paragraph, the nested style is applied through the end of the paragraph.

properties.name: EM_SPACE
properties.description: Uses the first em space as the nested style delimiter.

properties.name: EN_SPACE
properties.description: Uses the first en space as the nested style delimiter.

properties.name: NONBREAKING_SPACE
properties.description: Uses the first nonbreaking space as the nested style delimiter.

properties.name: AUTO_PAGE_NUMBER
properties.description: Uses the first automatic page number as the nested style delimiter.

properties.name: SECTION_MARKER
properties.description: Uses the first section name marker as the nested style delimiter.

description: Delimiter options for marking the end of the application of the nested style.
